result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th) and Operating w/ PAC (4th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Dawn M Littlegeorge was found guilty of OWI (4th), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: DA Gerald Fox appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person with Attorney Betthauser.  Plead guilty to OWI 4th.  Count 2 dismissed by operation of law.  Tracking traffic citation dismissed.  2 years probation.  Court advised the defendant of the charge and possible penalties of the charge she is pleading to.  Court confirmed the priors.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant understood.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.  Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of count 1.  Joint recommendation for 2 years probation.  Amending PAC one bracket down.  .17 - .19  PAC.  $900.00 fine.  DL rev and IID.  Defendant did not exercise her right to allocution.  Court ordered:  sentence withheld, 2 years probation.  $900.00 fine, plus costs.  Total $2,122.00.   215 days jail.  All but 1st 29 days stayed.  Any probation violation, the stay will be lifted.   Report date to be arranged through the probation agent. No later than 2/19/16 at 6 pm.   The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions. 36 mo. DL revocation and IID.  Alcohol assessment and driver's safety plan.
